item.title: Compiler Problem
item.dc:creator: @Monoxide Monoxide
item.description:
@Monoxide wrote:

Here use my nice and simple compiler @echo off if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit

just go to your compiler and right click then click edit
erase whats in there and put that in.

Hope it helps
